commit.message:
fix minor typo

daignose -> diagnose

feat: Provide reference lens data for VSCode

When client's experimental.codeLensFindReferences capability is set (only VSCode plugin now), Marksman will output extra data for the code lens command that can be used to implement client-side behavior to show references when clicking on the lens.
fix: Fix the range for wiki heading completion
misc: Add time tracking in Conn.update
misc: Use verbose output in marksman-server.bat

misc: Remove a warning about an unexpected version

The warning was long overdue for removal as it didn't reflect how the real editors do versioning (which is said because there's othewise no checksumming to ensure the states are consistent between the client and the server).

fix: Use UTF8 when encoding paths

Fixes #274
build: Bump snap dotnet to 8.0

deps: Bump versions

Serilog can't be upgraded because LSP lib needs v2
deps: Update fantomas and re-format

deps: Pull latest Ionide.LanguageServerProtocol

This corresponds to v0.4.21 with a few patches on top https://github.com/artempyanykh/LanguageServerProtocol/commit/df8b56eceaea10f5e7a05b906ef914484d5b3ad2
ci: Update dotnet version for GH actions
build: Upgrade to dotnet 8
fix: InternName.tryAsPath shouldn't crash on `/` root path link
Add download count to README.md
fix: helix: Use an empty array of commands for ExecuteCommandProvider cap as otherwise helix wont start
feat: Add code lenses with references for markdown link defs

feat: Add code lenses with '# of references' (server side)

This just provides a lens with something like '4 references' next to a header.
Clicking on the lens won't actually do anything yet because command handling needs to be implemented by every client.
misc: Add tests and a bit more logging around 'find references'

fix: Comparing to the wrong conn in paranoid mode

One of the previous commits introduced a bug where the 'from-scratch' state was compared to the previous state rather than the incrementally updated state.
fix: Fix a (silly) bug in MMap.difference
fix: Incorrect doc count in Fatality message
fix: Syms.Tag.toString() called itself recursively
core: Add config options to enable incremental references and paranoid mode
fix: Use relative paths for DocId format to be Windows-friendly

fix: Introduce (some) explicit dep tracking into Conn; squash bugs

At this point, incremental Conn seems to work (running for a while with paranoid mode on).
It still needs more testing and polish though.
refactor: Restructure Syms.Ref representation
dev: Introduce paranoid mode to streamline debug of incremental updates
fix: Fix a bug in link kind detection
refactor: Find references now uses connection graph
